01:16:51,390 --> 01:16:52,230
Oh, damn!

1019
01:16:59,020 --> 01:17:00,360
Shit!

1020
01:17:41,650 --> 01:17:43,360
Oh, my goodness.

1021
01:18:03,510 --> 01:18:05,340
What the hell is wrong with him?

1022
01:18:38,540 --> 01:18:40,830
My neck.

1023
01:18:40,920 --> 01:18:43,170
I broke my ribs.

1024
01:18:43,250 --> 01:18:45,920
It hurts. He's going to kill me.

1025
01:18:50,220 --> 01:18:51,390
Where is it?

1026
01:18:51,470 --> 01:18:53,680
What are you talking about?

1027
01:18:53,760 --> 01:18:56,180
The samples that you stole
from the factory in China.

1028
01:18:56,270 --> 01:18:58,850
What? What did I steal?

1029
01:19:00,150 --> 01:19:01,270
Mr. Seo.

1030
01:19:01,900 --> 01:19:03,650
If you return them,
you won't face charges.

1031
01:19:03,730 --> 01:19:05,280
-What?
-If you don't,

1032
01:19:05,360 --> 01:19:07,030
you'll go through criminal
and civil trials.

1033
01:19:07,400 --> 01:19:08,820
You'll sell your house, and go to jail.

1034
01:19:08,900 --> 01:19:11,530
What are you trying to say?

1035
01:19:13,420 --> 01:19:16,260
Are you crazy? I just quit my job

1036
01:19:16,340 --> 01:19:19,100
and came traveling here. Is that wrong?

1037
01:19:19,180 --> 01:19:20,310
There's nothing in his room.

1038
01:19:20,850 --> 01:19:21,850
You bastard!

1039
01:19:21,930 --> 01:19:24,310
Let go of me. You're hurting me!

1040
01:19:24,390 --> 01:19:26,730
You guys will pay for this.

1041
01:19:26,810 --> 01:19:29,770
I'm going to contact the embassy.
This is a diplomatic issue.

1042
01:19:29,860 --> 01:19:32,480
Do you have any evidence? Evidence, okay?

1043
01:19:33,030 --> 01:19:34,570
-This won't work.
-What?

1044
01:19:49,000 --> 01:19:52,000
Where am I?

1045
01:19:52,090 --> 01:19:53,300
In the middle of Wadi Rum.

1046
01:19:53,590 --> 01:19:55,720
What? Wadi Rum?

1047
01:20:08,900 --> 01:20:09,980
Thanks.

1048
01:20:18,610 --> 01:20:19,740
Come back. It's cold.

1049
01:20:41,800 --> 01:20:43,390
Mr. Seo, let me tell you again.

1050
01:20:44,010 --> 01:20:45,680
If you return them,
you won't face charges.

1051
01:20:45,770 --> 01:20:48,890
I really don't know.
Why are you doing this to me?

1052
01:20:48,980 --> 01:20:50,690
Hey, Geu-rae.

1053
01:20:51,150 --> 01:20:52,770
Why are you threatening me?

1054
01:20:53,360 --> 01:20:56,990
Am I an employee of your company?
Am I a Korean citizen?

1055
01:20:57,610 --> 01:20:58,950
Seriously.

1056
01:21:13,000 --> 01:21:13,840
Hello, Mr. Oh.

1057
01:21:15,170 --> 01:21:17,710
We caught him, but he won't talk.

1058
01:21:18,420 --> 01:21:21,010
Since we don't have any evidence,
we can't help it.

1059
01:21:21,340 --> 01:21:22,680
-Wait, Mr. Jang.
-What?

1060
01:21:24,050 --> 01:21:25,060
Russia.

1061
01:21:25,930 --> 01:21:27,720
Mafia mobsters' knee tattoo?

1062
01:21:28,310 --> 01:21:30,390
You see? Come on.

1063
01:21:30,480 --> 01:21:32,850
-I got it, sir.
-If you find the evidence,

1064
01:21:32,940 --> 01:21:34,230
I'll turn myself in.

1065
01:21:34,650 --> 01:21:36,940
Russia's Vasily Corp. is looking for you.

1066
01:21:38,150 --> 01:21:39,240
Mr. Cho.

1067
01:21:39,570 --> 01:21:42,200
How many stakes does the Russian
Mafia have in Vasily Corp.?

1068
01:21:42,950 --> 01:21:43,950
What?

1069
01:21:44,120 --> 01:21:47,990
According to Mr. Oh, it's over 70%.

1070
01:21:48,370 --> 01:21:49,540
Do you think it's true?

1071
01:21:52,580 --> 01:21:53,420
You're right.

1072
01:21:53,750 --> 01:21:57,210
I heard the mafia has been financing
the company in recent years.

1073
01:21:57,710 --> 01:21:59,510
However, I didn't know it's that high.

1074
01:22:00,220 --> 01:22:03,640
It's like the company is virtually owned
by the mafia.

1075
01:22:04,050 --> 01:22:05,140
Owned by the mafia?

1076
01:22:05,550 --> 01:22:06,680
Mr. Seo.

1077
01:22:07,310 --> 01:22:09,350
Mr. Oh asked me to deliver you a message.

1078
01:22:10,060 --> 01:22:12,310
What message?

1079
01:22:16,270 --> 01:22:17,650
In Russia,

1080
01:22:18,570 --> 01:22:20,240
drums beat, but laws are silent.

1081
01:22:21,570 --> 01:22:23,610
Jeez, I don't get it. Why are you...

1082
01:22:32,370 --> 01:22:33,370
Let's wrap up.

1083
01:22:34,080 --> 01:22:36,250
I'm whipping! I'm riding!

1084
01:22:36,840 --> 01:22:39,000
I'm whipping! I'm riding!

1085
01:22:51,560 --> 01:22:52,980
Where drums beat, laws are silent.

1086
01:22:59,860 --> 01:23:01,900
Tell me where you hid them.

1087
01:23:01,990 --> 01:23:03,570
They're my friends so let me talk to them.

1088
01:23:03,650 --> 01:23:04,490
Mr. Jang!

1089
01:23:04,570 --> 01:23:06,200
Amman Airport...

1090
01:23:07,160 --> 01:23:09,490
They're in a locker at Amman Airport.

1091
01:23:09,580 --> 01:23:12,410
The locker number is 28. I'm sorry.

1092
01:23:13,000 --> 01:23:15,750
I'm really sorry.
Please tell them to leave.

1093
01:23:19,380 --> 01:23:20,380
Mr. Jang.

1094
01:23:21,130 --> 01:23:22,760
You're indeed One International's
trading man.

1095
01:23:27,220 --> 01:23:28,970
How come he's One International's man?

1096
01:23:34,520 --> 01:23:36,060
Why is he One International's man?

1097
01:23:36,270 --> 01:23:38,310
It was just a figure of speech.

1098
01:23:38,400 --> 01:23:42,400
Mr. Jang made every effort
not to damage One International...

1099
01:23:42,480 --> 01:23:45,530
Why is it because of One International?
It's all for the sake of our company.

1100
01:23:45,610 --> 01:23:47,030
That's the same.

1101
01:23:47,110 --> 01:23:49,780
If One International gets damaged,
then your company will get damaged too.

1102
01:23:49,870 --> 01:23:51,700
-When your company gets damaged...
-Stop it!

1103
01:23:52,200 --> 01:23:55,660
Don't you know our company motto?
We may lose the work, but not our people.

1104
01:23:55,750 --> 01:23:58,580
I heard that's your own motto, sir.

1105
01:24:00,460 --> 01:24:02,090
Dong-sik, that punk.

1106
01:24:06,550 --> 01:24:07,760
Along the edge of the abyss

1107
01:24:08,050 --> 01:24:10,850
on the very brink of the precipice

1108
01:24:10,930 --> 01:24:14,810
I'm riding my horses, I'm whipping them!

1109
01:24:15,640 --> 01:24:17,190
You're a bad bastard.

1110
01:24:17,390 --> 01:24:18,810
I'm not.

1111
01:24:42,840 --> 01:24:44,130
-Hey, Geu-rae.
-Yes.

1112
01:24:44,210 --> 01:24:46,710
How come you didn't say anything when
they said One International man.

1113
01:24:46,920 --> 01:24:47,880
Sorry?

1114
01:24:48,170 --> 01:24:49,760
Any feelings left for One International?

1115
01:24:49,840 --> 01:24:50,840
No, sir.

1116
01:24:52,010 --> 01:24:54,970
Dude, you used to say you're satisfied
as long as you work as a regular employee.

1117
01:24:55,060 --> 01:24:56,310
Jeez, you said that.

1118
01:24:56,390 --> 01:24:59,850
Then a year later,
you become interested in higher salary

1119
01:24:59,940 --> 01:25:01,350
and more benefits, right?

1120
01:25:02,400 --> 01:25:05,280
That's right. Please increase my bonus.

1121
01:25:05,360 --> 01:25:06,360
What?

1122
01:25:19,000 --> 01:25:20,960
You really have no feelings left
for One International?

1123
01:25:21,670 --> 01:25:23,210
I don't know.

1124
01:25:23,380 --> 01:25:24,880
This punk.

1125
01:25:25,500 --> 01:25:27,760
-Convince me, sir.
-What?

1126
01:25:27,840 --> 01:25:29,340
Convince me, so that you can keep me.

1127
01:25:30,380 --> 01:25:33,720
What's your selling point, sir?

1128
01:25:35,010 --> 01:25:36,560
What's your selling point?

1129
01:25:36,810 --> 01:25:37,930
My efforts.

1130
01:25:38,180 --> 01:25:40,690
I haven't made any efforts so far,

1131
01:25:41,190 --> 01:25:43,020
so my efforts are freaking fresh and new.

1132
01:25:43,350 --> 01:25:45,060
What? How fresh and new?

1133
01:25:45,150 --> 01:25:46,320
I'll do my best.

1134
01:25:46,940 --> 01:25:48,530
I'll definitely do my best.

1135
01:25:49,280 --> 01:25:50,610
Just drive, punk!

1136
01:25:51,650 --> 01:25:54,200
I had a car accident before.
You shouldn't hit my head.

1137
01:25:54,280 --> 01:25:55,530
A road

1138
01:25:56,700 --> 01:26:00,250
is not just where we walk,
but also where we move forward.

1139
01:26:01,160 --> 01:26:02,750
A road where we cannot move forward

1140
01:26:03,710 --> 01:26:04,790
is not a real road.

1141
01:26:05,670 --> 01:26:07,710
A road is open to everyone.

1142
01:26:07,800 --> 01:26:09,050
What? Hazard pay?

1143
01:26:09,130 --> 01:26:11,630
But not everyone can take the road.

1144
01:26:12,220 --> 01:26:14,470
Are you in the army? What hazard pay?

1145
01:26:14,550 --> 01:26:17,180
You ordered me to catch him.
I risked my own life.

1146
01:26:17,260 --> 01:26:18,930
Jeez, you're so mean.

1147
01:26:19,020 --> 01:26:21,230
I'm on the road again.

1148
01:26:21,310 --> 01:26:23,140
Come on.

1149
01:26:23,230 --> 01:26:24,310
And

1150
01:26:26,610 --> 01:26:27,770
I'm not alone.

1151
01:27:49,940 --> 01:27:54,490
How can you leave us like this?

1152
01:27:56,360 --> 01:27:58,070
Oh no...

1153
01:27:58,780 --> 01:28:01,660
Honey...

1154
01:28:14,050 --> 01:28:15,880
EUN-JI KIM

1155
01:28:36,610 --> 01:28:38,530
Subtitle translation by You-jeong Kim
